2. The small gray cube and the small red cube are both cubes, but they differ in size and color from the large gray cylinder.

4. The yellow sphere and the purple sphere are spherical, but their curved surfaces and reflective finishes do not match the cylinder’s flat, circular top and bottom.  
5. No object in the image has the same shape as the large gray cylinder, as every other object is either a cube or a sphere with distinct geometric properties.  

<final> No, there is no other object with the same shape as the large gray cylinder.</final>
